- [ ] **Foundry track:** CFTC COT, USPTO patents, FDA approvals, Polymarket prediction markets, OpenSky M&A signals, container shipping, TreasuryDirect, EIA petroleum, USAspending contracts, Wikipedia spikes, calendar anomaly battery — target 30+ active features
- [ ] **Moonshot Sleeve track:** universe definition (Russell 2000 + recent IPO + theme-tagged), first edges (long-momentum, 52-week breakout, earnings beat+raise, insider clusters, FDA approval drift)
- [ ] **ML track:** Bayesian optimization replacing GA in Engine D

### September 2026 — Statistical ML upgrades + Foundry continuation

- [ ] Symbolic regression layer (PySR) operational
- [ ] Self-supervised time-series representations (TS2Vec) feeding meta-learner
- [ ] Causal discovery (PC algorithm) layer
- [ ] Foundry: 50+ active features, auto-ablation pruning weekly
- [ ] Pairs trading / cointegration sleeve operational
- [ ] Moonshot Sleeve backtest 2010-2024 validation

### October 2026 — Deployment infrastructure

- [ ] Real OMS replacing 22-line stub (retry, idempotency, partial fills, reconciliation)
- [ ] Portfolio-level vol-targeting
- [ ] Correlation-aware sizing
- [ ] Tail hedge sleeve (long 30-delta SPY puts, monthly roll)
- [ ] Portfolio-level kill switches
- [ ] Chaos engineering test harness
- [ ] Reconciliation cron (5-min cadence)
- [ ] **Gate 3 evaluation:** Sharpe ≥0.8 required to proceed to shadow-live

### November-December 2026 — Shadow-live

- [ ] Shadow-live mode online: same code path as live, paper-trades against Alpaca
- [ ] Continuous monitoring vs backtest expectations
- [ ] 90-day sustained run
- [ ] LLC formed for separate trading entity
- [ ] Public-facing scaffolding launched (Substack or equivalent)

### January 2027 — Final evaluation + first real money

- [ ] **Gate 4 evaluation:** sustained shadow-live Sharpe ≥1.0 over 90 days
- [ ] If pass: deploy $1,000 of real capital under same code path
- [ ] If fail: kill-thesis-D response triggered

---

## Public-facing scaffolding — start TODAY

### Why this matters

A live track record nobody knows about isn't worth much. **The audience IS the asset.** Building it from day 1 of a 12-month foundation period means by 2028, you have 2 years of public documentation. By 2030, four years. **Compounding credibility.**

### What to set up this week

1. **Pseudonymous Substack** — name like "Quant Garage" or "Solo Algo." NOT your real name yet.
2. **First post: "Why I'm building this"** — your goals A/B/C, the architecture overview, the kill thesis pre-commitments. Public, honest, dated.
3. **Monthly cadence** — last day of each month, post containing:
   - That month's OOS Sharpe number (deterministic)
   - Any gate evaluations
   - What was learned, what was wrong
   - What's next
4. **No promises, no predictions of future returns** — just documentation of what was built and what was measured

### Why pseudonymous to start

- Reduces psychological pressure during failures
- Lets you walk away from the public identity if the project fails the kill thesis
- When you want to formalize (RIA, fund), can transition to real name with track record intact
- Until you have something verified-by-others, public real-name commitments are premature

### What NOT to put in public

- Specific trade ideas, signals, edges (capacity protection)
- Your own positions or returns in dollar amounts
- Anything that could be construed as advice
- The exact gauntlet criteria (lets people game it)

---

## GIPS-compliance scaffolding — from day 1 of real money

When real money flows in 2027, every record needed for audited performance reporting must already exist. Set up now:

- [ ] **Time-weighted return calculation** matching CFA Institute methodology
- [ ] **Daily portfolio valuation** captured + archived
- [ ] **Trade-by-trade ledger** with reasoning, signal source, expected outcome
- [ ] **Independent custodian** (Alpaca acceptable; later Schwab/IB for RIA)
- [ ] **Fee transparency** documentation
- [ ] **Quarterly performance attestation** (self-attested at first; audited later)
- [ ] **Composite definition** for SMA business later

When you're ready to go pro in 2028+, having 12+ months of GIPS-track-able records is the difference between "credible" and "starting from scratch."

---

## What you can do TONIGHT (or as soon as you're back at your laptop)

**These three actions, this week, are the highest-leverage moves available:**

1. **Drop this document into `docs/Core/path_to_1pct.md`** — sign with today's date. Commit. This becomes the load-bearing artifact for the next 12 months.

2. **Drop the kill thesis pre-commitments into `docs/Core/kill_thesis.md`** — separate document, dated, signed, immutable. Future-you cannot rewrite this without leaving git evidence.

3. **Set up the Substack tonight.** Name it. Write the first post: "Why I'm building this." 600-1000 words. Includes: your three goals, the kill thesis numbers, the 12-month timeline, the commitment to monthly updates. Publish. **The act of publishing is the commitment.**

---

## What "undeniable" looks like at the end of Year 1

By 2027-04-30:
- 12 months of dated, public documentation of the journey
- Foundation Gate cleared (Sharpe ≥1.0 deterministic) — or kill thesis triggered honestly
- Engine C real optimizer + Engine E HMM regime detection in production
- 50+ Tier-B features in Foundry, auto-pruning monthly
- Moonshot Sleeve operational with backtest validation
- Real OMS + tail hedge + chaos-tested kill switches
- 90+ days of sustained shadow-live agreement
- $1,000 in real capital running for 90 days post-shadow

By 2027-12-31:
- 18+ months of live + shadow public track record
- LLC formed, GIPS-compliant records since real money started
- 5,000+ Substack subscribers (if monthly updates have been honest and substantive)
- First friends-and-family conversation about SMAs (if Year 1 results justify)

By 2028-12-31 (Year 3):
- 12 months of real-money live track record
- RIA registration filed
- 1-3 friends/family SMAs running ($1-5M AUM)
- Substack at 10,000+ paid subscribers if monetized

By 2030 (Year 5):
- $25M+ AUM at RIA OR
- $200k+/year newsletter revenue OR
- Both

**The path to top 1% is dated. Each gate has a number. Each gate has a kill thesis response. The work is parallel-tracked. The audience is built from day 1.**

---

## The single most important thing about this plan

**It's not optional that the kill thesis numbers stick.** The reason most retail quant projects fail isn't that the system was wrong — it's that the operator rationalized past the moments where the data said "stop." **Pre-registering the kill thesis with dates and numbers, in public on a Substack and in a git-tracked doc, is the single most powerful discipline mechanism available.**

If May 31 OOS Sharpe lands at 0.35, the response is **not** "let me rerun with different parameters." The response is the pre-committed structural review. **Otherwise the entire plan is a fiction.**

The path is the path. The work is parallel. The gates are real. Sign the document, set up the Substack, and start. Today is day 1.

